file_content.text: Pathetic.
I did not see Seros. You were successful?
I brought his effects, as you asked.
Yes.
Good.
Take a look for yourself.
Was there any doubt?
I didn't have any difficulty dispatching my Jedi.
More than you.
Only Jedi would call something this fragile "Battlemaster."
We still have living targets to appraise.
Let's keep looking forward.
Indeed.
Battlemaster some sort of special honor?
Battlemaster?
Before our return, Jun Seros taught all Jedi the art of conflict.
Killed a few Sith in my time, Tormen.
Think you'd fair better?
Then they were feeble. The Sith are stronger for having such weakness stamped out.
His death is a crippling blow to the Jedi order. And without Jun Seros at his side, the Supreme Chancellor is exposed.
Victory is close.
That's going to get us the Supreme Chancellor?
Is it the intel you wanted?
Well...? What's the big score?
It's encoded with Jun Seros's bioscan.
Gonna pay for that, or browse all day?
I want my credits.
Your compensation will be appropriate.
Once the encryption is broken, we will know this data's true value.
You know more than you're letting on.
What do you expect to find?
Jun Seros came here aboard the Founder. He was privy to its security protocols, landing codes, even the Supreme Chancellor's itinerary.
I didn't come this far to let the big catch get away.
I'll keep my fingers crossed.
I will have the Supreme Chancellor's head.
I've had my fill of sitting around.
And how long will that take?
You may go.
My subordinates will transmit the relevant data to your vessel when it is prepared.
Until then, do as you wish.
Until then, make yourself useful to Darth Decimus. The battle for Corellia is not yet decided.
A large Republic fleet has entered the system. It includes the Founder, Supreme Chancellor Janarus's personal flagship.
These reinforcements are attempting to consolidate at the Green Gardens. You know who leads them.
Seros has been spotted?
A certain Jedi?
He is a conspicuous leader.
Looks like your plan is working.
That's great!
What are the Green Gardens?
Green Gardens?
A fortress with window dressing.
It's about time we saw some results.
Finally.
Jun Seros hopes to rally the remnants of the Green Jedi.
Jun Seros seeks to urge Coronet City's Green Jedi out of their enclave and press the attack.
When their forces are amassed, the Republic will attempt one last offensive. You have until then to reap your vengeance.
I'll keep my visit short.
Understood.
I work at my own pace.
You're giving me a time limit?
If Seros leads his attack, he will die. I will not surrender ground for your vendetta.
Attacking Jun Seros within his headquarters is the only way to be sure crucial data is in his possession.
I could care less about Seros. Show me the bottom line.
I'd rather reap credits.
To collect the Supreme Chancellor's head, you will require the information in Seros's possession.
Dispose of Seros. Quietly. No one must know of his demise. Bring his effects to me.
Prepare the commissioner for the surrender.
My lord!
Your success is noted.
Anyone else you're planning to add to this gathering?
What's our next move?
Your work is done, for now.
So's your gratitude.
Another satisfied customer.
When do I get the real prize, Tormen?
Enough small time jobs.
Soon.
Enjoy the fruits of your labor. Watch these rebels sign our enemies' death warrant.
Might as well see this through.
If you wish.
I was in the mood to take in a show.
Good idea.
The Empire is interested in mutual cooperation and prosperity, not stomping out our democracy.
The people will thank you for coming to this peaceful resolution. They're the ones who really suffer from all this political feuding.
Supreme Chancellor Janarus, I implore you: Ratify this treaty. Show the galaxy that the Republic still believes in freedom of choice!
Did you enjoy my first public address?
You're cut out for politics, Darbin.
I liked it.
Ha, diplomatic of you. I'll take it as a compliment.
Your performance will be judged by its results.
Ah, ahem--yes. You won't be disappointed.
Never seen a rat speak so eloquently.
Two-faced scum.
Hey--that hurts. I worked hard to get us all this far.
Continue to.
Right--of course, my lord.
There you have it, Senators. A peaceful resolution, negotiated and sealed with the full endorsement of the opposition party.
Your Republic has failed them for the last time. Corellia has chosen Imperial rule.
Supreme Chancellor Janarus will ratify this treaty and withdraw Republic forces from Corellia today. Or the Core Worlds will see a true invasion. You have one day.
Supreme Chancellor Janarus, respected members of the Galactic Senate, the Corellian people have chosen.
We will not continue to be held captive by a failed system.
I ask, no--I demand that Supreme Chancellor Janarus ratify this treaty and acknowledge Corellia as a sovereign system of the Sith Empire.
It was only a matter of time. As prime minister for life, let me be the first to welcome you to Imperial Corellia, my lord.
Had you delivered what you promised, you would enjoy a longer reign.
If there's nothing else....
We done here, Tormen?
Make yourself comfortable. The trap is set.
That how you conclude all your business?
Should I be concerned?
When the agreement is not upheld.
Not a bad performance; I especially liked that last act.
That was good fun.
Now, we wait.
Just call me when you've got something.
This is your win, not mine.
Do not stray far.
Darth Tormen desires your presence immediately. This way, please.
The trap is nearly set. All that remains is to capture the last figurehead of Corellia's old regime: Corellia's civil police force commissioner.
Somehow, Commissioner Carter survived the initial purge of dissenters before Prime Minister Falcone delivered Corellia to us.
Did the assassination attempt spook him into hiding?
Has he gone underground?
Hardly.
I'd have thought Corellia'd be under martial law by now.
Are the police still active?
CorSec was disbanded, officially. One of many steps taken to ensure a smooth exchange of power. It failed.
I'm almost tempted to handle this one no charge. Almost.
Too bad. I hate cops.
Since the purge, Commissioner Carter has rallied the rebellion. The public sees him as the last legitimate voice of the Corellian people.
Carter and his CorSec officers are the backbone of the civilian resistance.
Clobbering the local hero ought to take the fight out of them.
Time to break it.
Shattering the people's convictions will be all too easy.
CorSec is one thing, but I'm not keen on dragging any more bystanders into this war.
No more killing civilians.
It will not be an issue.
Imperial troops can't handle a bunch of lousy beat cops?
Big whoop.
The threat they pose isn't direct. They've trained throngs of combatants and guided thousands of Republic troops behind our lines.
CorSec's old headquarters is now a formidable fortress. Our forces are laying siege to it as we speak.
Their standing orders are to block off any escape. That is all.
I won't be calling for backup.
Understood.
Can't we coordinate something?
What if I need assistance?
There will be no assaults until you have secured the commissioner.
I prefer not having your grunts underfoot.
Good. They won't be in my way.
Contact me when Commissioner Carter is in custody. My troops will cover your exit.
Your representative, Darth Tormen.
Impressive, for an animal.
Our next objective is to bring Corellia's beasts to heel. You will be the one to break them.
How do you plan for me to do that?
Give me the specifics.
Broken I can do.
Shouldn't be a problem.
You want an animal handler? Find a circus.
I hunt. I don't train.
Silence.
The Corellians cohabit with a number of species. The most numerous and organized are the Selonians.
The Republic needs to see the Selonians accede to the Empire. A representative must be acquired.
There someone specific you have your eye on?
Who do you want?
Never seen a Selonian. What am I looking for?
Selonians?
Man-sized vermin, with enough intelligence to fear us. They support the rebellion from Coronet City's interstitial maintenance corridors.
And you want me to grab your token Selonian. I get it.
Get to the point.
No, not just any mongrel. I require a rebel. A ringleader.
One particularly tenacious animal leads packs of raiders to undermine our front lines. It will make as good an example as any.
General Krau will brief you on the battle plan. When you have the creature, bring it to me in Axial Park.
You'll have your Selonian soon.
Understood.
Planning to take it for a walk?
Sounds like a lovely time.
Got someplace more important to be?
You going somewhere?
I lead from the front.
Do not keep me waiting.
Trying to locate the Selonian raiders in the guts of Coronet City would be almost futile.
Instead, you'll target an invaluable Selonian resource, and force these raiders to defend it.
What's important enough that they'd risk fighting on our terms?
It'll have to be good bait.
I was getting tired of chasing all my targets down anyway.
Nice change of pace.
Follow the plan exactly, and they'll have nowhere to run.
Assuming there'll be anything left to defend.
Better hope they act fast.
Your objective isn't destruction, it's ransom.
Selonians rely on a small breeding caste to reproduce. With their future at stake, the Selonians will have no choice but to act.
Raid the Selonian warrens under Labor Valley, take your hostages and hold them at these coordinates.
What's so special about this section of tunnels?
Why there?
It's a dead end. They'll believe they have you cornered right up to the moment you cut off their only route of escape.
There's no glory in bullying the weak.
I don't like this plan.
Picking a fight with civilians hardly seems sporting.
I don't like this plan.
Once you begin pulling the mothers from their dens, even the "civilians" will attack you with unmitigated ferocity.
And if the Selonians aren't getting the message?
Can I leverage the hostages?
Use your discretion. So long as the their leader is captured, the others are expendable.
These shock collars will keep the alien filth in line while you lead them to the ambush coordinates.
When your objective is complete, report directly to Darth Tormen in Axial Park. Just follow the sound of destruction.
You've obtained Chairman Fane. Good. We proceed on schedule.
General, see to the bounty hunter's reward.
Yes, my lord.
